What is DNS?

Domain Name System which translates the human-friendly hostnames into the machine IP addresses
www.google.come ===> 172.217.18.36
DNS is the backbone on the internet
DNS uses a hierarchical naming structure
  .com
  example.com
  www.example.com
  api.example.com

DNS terminologies

Domain Registrar: Amazon Router 53, GoDaddy
DNS Records: A, AAAA, CNAME, NS
Zone file: Contains DNS records
Name Server: Resolves DNS queries (auth/non auth)
Top Level Domains (TLD): .com .us .in .gov .edu .org
Second Level Domain (SLD)  amazon.com  google.com

How DNS works?
